##Good-bye, Dr Li Wenliang

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

On the morning of February 7, a member of the public at Wuhan Central Hospital offered flowers to mourn the death of Li Wenliang, a doctor who died of pneumonia. A receipt was found in the bouquet. This is the hospital district where Li Wenliang worked. At 3:48 am on February 7, the official Weibo Account of Wuhan Central Hospital announced that Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at the hospital, died at 2:58 am on February 7 after intensive rescue efforts failed. Reporter of Zhongqing newspaper Zhongqing Net, photo by Li Shizheng
